Jochen, in-memory compilation is still supported, but in-file compilation is changed to rely on the same 
 normal official API, e.g. `javax.tools.JavaCompiler`. As a result, we can compile all source code in the same way and it will be easier for us to maintain.

@blackdrag 
As far as I know, `javax.tools.JavaCompiler` is a normal official API and will not stop working suddenly, isn't it?  :wink:
https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/javax/tools/JavaCompiler.html

@blackdrag @paulk-asert 

To sum up, the current implementation supports compiling Java stubs(in-memory and in-file) in the same way via the normal standard API `javax.tools.JavaCompiler`, which can eliminate Jochen's worries. 

